    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 22, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🏛️ The Iran vote got hidden under the rug\n\nCongress came close to using the war-powers lever, so House GOP leadership discovered the elegant doctrine of not voting.\n\n- **The retreat:** AP says Republicans called off a Thursday House vote on forcing Trump to withdraw from the Iran war after it became clear they lacked the votes to defeat it.\n- **The math:** Democrat Gregory Meeks said supporters had the votes; Axios says Jared Golden was ready to flip to yes, joining prior Republican defectors Brian Fitzpatrick, Thomas Massie, Warren Davidson and Tom Barrett.\n- **The deadline:** the 1973 War Powers Resolution gives presidents 60 days before Congress must authorize conflict, and that clock has now become the problem nobody wants on the floor.\n\n*Democracy, but only after attendance improves.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/iran-war-donald-trump-congress-vote-8038c7f9552186716d01f910d6a0d356) | [Axios](https://www.axios.com/2026/05/21/house-iran-war-powers-vote)\n\n---\n\n## 🧭 Rubio took the reassurance tour north\n\nNATO allies asked whether the U.S. commitment still exists; Washington sent Marco Rubio with a smile and several caveats.\n\n- **The meeting:** Rubio is attending NATO foreign ministers' talks in Helsingborg, Sweden, while Pentagon officials brief the alliance on U.S. force commitments in Europe.\n- **The anxiety:** AP says allies are watching possible troop reductions, Ukraine support and the fallout from the Iran war, including U.S. frustration with NATO help on Hormuz.\n- **The agenda:** NATO says ministers are preparing the Ankara summit around defense spending, industrial output and long-term Ukraine support.\n\n*The transatlantic relationship remains strong enough to require constant reassurance.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/4ad6e39e0c31d14b89b419906acbb6dc) | [NATO](https://www.nato.int/en/news-and-events/articles/news/2026/05/20/secretary-general-highlights-how-allies-are-stepping-up-ahead-of-foreign-ministers-meeting-in-sweden)\n\n---\n\n## 🕊️ Gaza's ceasefire got a disarmament invoice\n\nThe peace plan has reached the familiar Middle East milestone: everyone agrees on the framework, then fights over the part that matters.\n\n- **The UN push:** AP says Nickolay Mladenov urged the Security Council to use every tool available to press Hamas to disarm under the U.S.-brokered Gaza ceasefire.\n- **The other side:** Mladenov also said Israel must meet its obligations, citing Palestinian killings and restrictions on humanitarian aid flows since the October ceasefire.\n- **The blockage:** the Board of Peace says reconstruction, Israeli withdrawals and a new Palestinian government remain stuck while Hamas links disarmament to Israeli pullback.\n\n*Ceasefire implementation: where road maps go to become parking lots.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/2d4c4a8e57aa6bbfa07a25c6cb4bbd23)"
  }
]
